<http://open-services.net/ns/auto/shapes/2.1#DialogShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "Dialog" .
<http://open-services.net/ns/auto/shapes/2.1#DialogShape> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "Dialogs in general are defined by OSLC Core 2.0, and this specification defines two specific types of dialogs: the immediate-execution creation dialog, which can be used to allow a user to interactively create a new Automation request which is immediately available for execution, and the deferred-execution creation dialog, which creates a new Automation Request that is not immediately available for execution, but which requires further work on the part of the consumer."^^<http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral> .
